          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <p>fos. 1r-15v: The anonymous introduction to the Decretum, "In
              prima parte agitur," complete, but omitting the de
              consecratione.</p>
              <p>fo. 16r-v: Blank.</p>
              <p>fos. 17r-178v: The first recension of the Decretum, ending
              defectively with the end of C. 12. The manuscript once continued
              with C. 13 (and, probably, the rest of the Decretum, as is evident
              from the catchword at the bottom of fo. 178v:
              "&lt;D&gt;iocesi///". A later hand added, in the margins and on
              additional leaves, second-recension texts missing in the original
              text of the manuscript.</p>
              <p>fos. 179r-180v: Fragment of a glossed Bible, Numbers 2: 27-3:
              18.</p>
            </objectDesc>
          </physDesc>
        </msDesc>
